<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>convince myself I was doing it for everybody else's own good and they would someday celebrate me as a hero. I would mostly be into vigilantism of the over-the-top poetic justice variety. My goal would be to reform the world by assassinating evil people in positions of power to give good people room to accomplish their goals. Sadly, my vision would become corrupted as I also started going after not-entirely-evil people who just pissed me off.</p>
<p>I don't actually like being in charge of stuff, it's stressful. Therefore I would find a person who BELIEVES themselves to be the world's greatest supervillain and has a huge ego and be their <a href="https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheCreon">trusted personal aide</a>. My generally intelligent but narrowminded, self-absorbed and not very curious boss would be on a simple mission such as trying to take over the world. I would make sure the information they preferred to rely on to make future plans appeared to present the people I wanted to assassinate as direct threats or obstacles to the boss's rise to power. If the boss ever got too close to succeeding, or if my indirect vigilantism ever eliminated enough people to satisfy me<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-994067-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-994067-1')">1</a></sup> I would arrange an accident for the boss, then turn to the legitimate authorities and confess everything, plead for clemency and assist with an orderly shutdown of the boss's crime network. (Carefully preserving small portions of it for my own later use.) I would then write a tell-all memoir on my experiences and go on the talk show circuit to promote it.</p>
<p>I <em>might</em> have some minor telekinesis powers - maybe enough to get a soda out of the fridge, hold open an elevator door or give somebody a fatal aneurysm in a pinch. That's optional though.</p>
<p>My main power would be a mind-affecting one, and I'm not sure there's a single word to describe it. It would be the power to suppress, in other people, the ability to perform the mental shift from &quot;making a decision&quot; to &quot;acting on that decision.&quot; Might be related to executive function, but I'm not sure if that's the right sciencey term. For example, a hero could point a gun at me and <em>want</em> and <em>intend</em> to fire. But I could squelch their mind's ability to translate that intent into an actual movement of the muscles in their trigger finger. So they wouldn't.</p>
<p>I would use this power sparingly enough that virtually no one &#8212; <em>especially</em> not my supervillain boss &#8212; knew that I had it. It would just turn out that sometimes, my boss might be about to do something I didn't like, or might be mad at me and about to order one of their goons to shoot me, and they just&#8230; wouldn't. People being people, they would rationalize it to themselves after the fact as their own decision.</p>
</div>
</div>
