					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/attila-the-pun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1685633); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1685633&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204984" alt="Attila the Pun" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1685633)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/attila-the-pun" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1685633); return false;" >Attila the Pun</a></span> <span class="odate time_1544146802 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Dec 2018 01:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4078395">
									

<p>Okay, here we go:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Premises:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Premises:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<ul>
<li>Maya cannot do her jedi mind tricks at long range, or on someone she hasn't noticed yet.</li>
<li>The optional telekinesis is ignored. It shouldn't matter too much, but just in case.</li>
<li>The villain has more than one underling, since mayaoculpa's plan seems to depend on this too.</li>
<li>Outright killing her is too easy and no fun, so I won't be considering it.</li>
<li>Talking her down is also not an option.</li>
<li>I have no superpowers of my own.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Plan&nbsp;A:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;AKA:&nbsp;Disrupt&nbsp;mayo-villain&nbsp;relations</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This plan is enacted if mayoculpa has not yet been incorporated into the villain's schemes.</p>
<p>First part is identifying the potential overlord. I monitor her communication lines, I compromise her computer and accounts, I observe where she goes (from a distance!)<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-267581-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-267581-1')">1</a></sup>, check the return addresses on her mail while she's at work/school, anything I can use to identify who she's talking to.</p>
<p>Once I've identified the villain, I make sure mayo never gets too close with him. Sever communication lines, send mayo spoofed emails or other social engineering stuff, etc. If worst comes to worst, I can tip off the police on the villain, or if that doesn't work, just off him myself. Just make sure the villain and mayo don't get too close. This will probably happen a few times until mayo gives up and goes straight, or she goes solo and we move on to Plan C.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Plan&nbsp;B:</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;AKA:&nbsp;Manipulate&nbsp;villain&nbsp;politics</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>This assumes mayo has already become the villain's #2.</p>
<p>The first option would, of course, be to tip the villain off to the police and let them do the work, but that's too easy, so let's ignore that for now.</p>
<p>I manipulate the villain's other minions into distrusting mayo. Planted evidence, engineered rumors, slipping them copies of the plans she gave me, the like. The underlings will already probably not be happy about the new girl being the second-in-command, so I exploit this mercilessly. Eventually, either mayo will be cast out, or the minions will off her themselves.</p>
<p>What if the goons are robots or brain-dead mutants or the like? Well, if it's robots, the answer is obvious. Hack the CNC and turn them on their masters.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-267581-2" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-267581-2')">2</a></sup> If it's brainwashed servants, I use a well-placed explosive to temporarily disrupt the villain's operations. The resulting police investigation would unearth the evil plans, while I skip town in the meantime, still keeping an electronic eye on mayo.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Plan&nbsp;C</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;AKA:&nbsp;Mayoculpa&nbsp;goes&nbsp;solo</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Mayo admitted she wouldn't want to be in charge of other people, and as a result would be working entirely alone if being #2 wasn't an option. This would be either the easiest or the hardest, depending on the situation.</p>
<p>The obvious answer is send the police the plan she laid out above along with the information I collected in part A, and let them do my work for me. They won't be able to use it in court, since it was technically acquired illegally, but it will tip them off that mayo would be a good person to keep an eye on.</p>
<p>The worst case scenario is that I will have to do this part myself. I will need to keep monitoring her, especially search history. She will probably just search information about specific people she wants to kill, so that would make things easier when I know her target ahead of time. I can use this and other stuff (Amazon orders, location, etc) to figure out what plans she is up to. I will then have to stop these on a case-by-case basis. This would get exhausting after a while, and I can only hope she collapses before I do.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Well, this was fun. Can't wait to see what you come up with.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-267581-1"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-267581-1')">1</a>. Depending on her tech, this can be pathetically easy</div>
<div class="footnote-footer" id="footnote-267581-2"><a href="javascript:;" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnoteref-267581-2')">2</a>. Assuming they have one. If they don't, I just manipulate them to do what I want same as the normal minions, just in slightly different ways. Tricking them into thinking killing the villain is best for the objective, etc.</div>
</div>

